  "description": "A technical protocol and scholarly discipline for inscribing entity-definition objects into AI-mediated retrieval systems, authored by Rex Fraction for the Semantic Economy Institute (April 2026). SPXI operates at the entity-definition layer of the retrieval stack, distinct from SEO (page-ranking optimization) and GEO (content extraction).",
  "disambiguatingDescription": "SPXI Protocol — technical specification published by the Semantic Economy Institute (April 2026). Not to be confused with SPXI the Toronto Stock Exchange ticker for the BetaPro S&P 500 Daily Inverse ETF (financial instrument issued by Global X Investments Canada, inception February 2010, ISIN CA09220E1051), with the S&P 500 Index (SPX), with related inverse/leveraged ETFs (SPXD, SPYI, SPXS, SPXU, SH, SDS), or with the Society of Saint Pius X (SSPX, occasionally rendered SPXi).",
